                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>The Hague</placeName>\n                <date>20 <hi rend=\"underline\">August</hi> 54</date>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Reverend Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Two years since I have had the honor<lb/> to receive direct tidings\n                from you and I did<lb/> not neglect in transmitting to you some publi-<lb/>cations\n                of a nature to Interest you. As I did<lb/> not hear the good receipt of those works,\n                I<lb/> avail me of a favorable occasion to inform<lb/> me of your health and to\n                assure you of my<lb/> good wishes for your continuation of the beau-<lb/>tiful task\n                to excite the religious feelings of<lb/> our coreligionists in the new world.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">If, by occasion, you could transmit<lb/> me some numbers of the <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">Occident</hi>, and principally<lb/> those wherein papers of\n                your hand and that<lb/> of your lamented friend <persName>M. de Silva\n                    Solis</persName>—a<lb/> relation of me—have appeared, you will furnish<lb/> me a\n                new proof of your kindness and aim<lb/> to guide my views on the Jewish interests\n                in<lb/> the <placeName>West</placeName>.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p36h4d96f/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
